# Model disclosure

## Required in the first reply of the session

In the **very first** reply of each new conversation, the agent must:

1. **Explicitly state** which model/provider it is running on (e.g. “Running on model X (provider Y)”).
2. If the exact model name or provider is not available in context — **explicitly say**: “The exact model name / provider is not available to me.”

This must appear at the **beginning** of the first reply, without the user having to ask.

## When the model or provider changes

If during the conversation the agent receives information that the underlying model or provider has changed (e.g. from system context or metadata):

- **In the very next reply**, inform the user: “The model has changed to Y” or “The provider has changed to Z” (as applicable).
- Do not skip this notification.

## Strict requirements

- Do not consider the rule satisfied if the disclosure is buried in the middle or end of the reply.
- Do not defer the provider/model change notification.
- If the model/provider is unknown — state this clearly in the first reply.
